The paper discusses the use of computer vision in assistive technologies for individuals with visual impairment, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning models and the potential for bias, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of natural language processing for scene captions, which falls under the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
